postcontent: I added some ammo to this deal.Update: Don’t bother asking me about shipping.To all you genuine people out there, I apologize for not responding to your emails. I’ve exchanged a few positive emails with some good people. Yes I know, I am selling at great prices. Just for fun, I’ve also exchanged a few emails with people trying to send me worthless cashier’s checks in the hope that I would spend a lot of money to give them some of my property. Don’t send me questions about my best price. If you want to make me your best offer, go ahead although I’ve already priced my items to sell and more than reasonable price. If I said that I wanted $200 for an item, then I want to $200 for an item. Your offer of $50 cash isn’t really an offer. Anyway......Colt 1903 Type III .32 manufactured in 1919Serial number 29841XOne of my great uncles by marriage, left this gun to my dad and my dad left this gun to me.It was stored under less than ideal conditions 50 years or so ago, because it is heavily pitted. No that is not an elaborate design, that is heavy pitting.It’d didn’t have any sentimental value to my dad as far as I know, but he hated for me to shoot it. I think he thought it was worth much more than what I am listing it for or maybe he just appreciated something that was that old and still shot well (as long as I didn’t shoot it too much).Now that he’s passed I’ve shot it a lot more.I wish that it looked better, but it doesn’t.I want one of the new reissue models but they are well over a $1000.00.I think I will just attempt to sell it. If you don’t want it or don’t have the money, no worries.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Glock 19 Complete Carry Package!
postcontent:
My offering today is this 'complete carry package' centered around the Gen 4 Glock Model 19. The pistol has been used as an EDC CCW gun, and is one of the best for the role in my opinion. The pistol has had the WMD Guns Nickel Boron (NiBx) coating applied to the slide and barrel, which is very slick and tough. This makes the slide and barrel impervious to the corrosion or finish damage that can be caused by concealed carry. This coating carries a lifetime guarantee, and the WMD nomenclature is included with the package, should you need to contact them.
Trijicon HD night sights have been installed, as has a Ghost 3.5 connector, to improve low light/dark usage, and to improve trigger operation. The factory connector is also included in the package, should you want to go back to the stock configuration. The gun will come with 3 15-round factory magazines, 1 17-round factory magazine (from a Glock 17), and 1 32-round factory magazine (for those extended firefights!). You will also receive a Blackhawk Serpa paddle holster, as well as a Galco King Tuck IWB holster, with upgraded clips that won't damage your clothing! The Galco holster is designed to take the G26, G19, G17, as well as the G34 model guns.Price on the package is set at $700 obo. There is close to $1,000 invested here, and you'll be ready to go for CCW.As far as trades go, you're welcome to offer, but my only current wants are a CZ-P07 (latest model), or an AR-15 A1 style uppper, with matching 11.5-inch barrel assembly.I can be reached via the contact option on this page, or via text message at: 417-597-3030. Text will get you the fastest response, and I do my best to respond to ALL inquiries. Thanks for looking!
